Project Report on Healthcare System Using Agile
1. Introduction

A Healthcare System is used to manage hospital activities like patient records, doctor appointments, and billing. This project aims to provide an easy system for hospitals to handle patient data digitally. Agile methodology is used for better planning and continuous improvements.

2. Objective

To store patient details securely

To manage doctor appointments

To generate bills and reports

To reduce manual paperwork

3. Scope

Modules included:

Patient registration

Doctor details management

Appointment booking

Medical history record

Billing system

Reports (basic)

4. Agile Implementation

Agile helps to build the system in multiple sprints and add features gradually.

Sprint Plan

Sprint 1: Patient registration + doctor module
Sprint 2: Appointment booking
Sprint 3: Billing + reports
Sprint 4: Testing + final deployment

5. Tools & Technologies

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript

Backend: Java / Python / PHP

Database: MySQL

Tools: VS Code, GitHub

6. Conclusion

Healthcare system makes hospital work easier and faster. Agile helped to complete the project in phases with proper testing and improvements after every sprint.
